The error "android.os.NetworkOnMainThreadException" is thrown when you perform a network operation on the main thread of your Android application. Network operations, such as reading from a URL, should be performed on a separate thread to avoid blocking the UI thread.

To fix this issue, you should wrap your network code in an 'AsyncTask' or use a thread explicitly. For example:

new Thread(new Runnable() {
   @Override
   public void run() {
      try {
         URL url = new URL(urlToRssFeed);
         SAXParserFactory factory = SAXParserFactory.newInstance();
         SAXParser parser = factory.newSAXParser();
         XMLReader xmlreader = parser.getXMLReader();
         RssHandler theRSSHandler = new RssHandler();
         xmlreader.setContentHandler(theRSSHandler);
         InputSource is = new InputSource(url.openStream());
         xmlreader.parse(is);
      } catch (Exception e) {
         e.printStackTrace();
      }
   }
}).start();

