The error "Collection was modified; enumeration operation may not execute" occurs when you modify the collection being iterated over during a foreach loop.

In your code, you have the method UnsubscribeEvent that modifies the subscribers dictionary while the NotifySubscribers method is looping through it using a foreach loop.

To fix the issue, you need to make the subscribers dictionary thread-safe. One way to do this is by using a ConcurrentDictionary instead of a Dictionary, since ConcurrentDictionary provides thread-safe access to its elements. You can modify the code as follows:

csharp

private static ConcurrentDictionary<Guid, Subscriber> subscribers;
public SubscriptionServer()
{            
    subscribers = new ConcurrentDictionary<Guid, Subscriber>();
}

And when you want to iterate through the subscribers, use the Values property of the ConcurrentDictionary:

scss

foreach(Subscriber s in subscribers.Values)

This way, you can avoid the "Collection was modified; enumeration operation may not execute" error even if the subscribers dictionary is being modified by multiple threads simultaneously.

