public async void Foo()
{
    // Asynchronous method body
}

public void Bar()
{
    // Synchronous method body
    Task.Run(() => Foo()).Wait();
}
Note that using Wait blocks the calling thread until the asynchronous method Foo completes. If you need to perform other work while waiting for the asynchronous method to complete, you can use the Task.WhenAny method.

Also, it is important to note that the use of async void should be avoided in most cases, as it can make it difficult to handle exceptions and it doesn't allow the caller to wait for the completion of the asynchronous operation. A better approach is to use async Task and return the Task object to the caller, which can then use the await keyword or the .Wait method to wait for the asynchronous operation to complete.

