To make a Python class serializable, you need to implement the json.JSONEncoder interface by defining default() method. In this method you can return a dictionary of the class instance's attributes, and it will be used as the JSON representation of the object. Here's an example:

python

import json

class FileItem:
    def __init__(self, fname):
        self.fname = fname
        
    def default(self):
        return {'fname': self.fname}

