You use static methods when you want a method to be invoked on a class rather than on an instance of the class. The method should be declared as static.

A static method does not have access to instance variables and methods, only static variables and methods. If you have a method that does not depend on the state of an instance, and you don't need to access instance variables or methods, you should make it static.

Example:

javascript

class Obj {
  static void someMethod() {
    // do something
  }
}

// Invoke the static method
Obj.someMethod();

